  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HSSEQ & Training Executive",
  "description": "<h3>Role Overview</h3><p>The HSSEQ & Training Executive supports the company’s Health, Safety, Security, Environment and Quality (HSSEQ) framework, ensuring compliance with maritime regulations and promoting a strong safety culture across operations.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Support implementation and maintenance of HSSEQ policies, procedures, and training programs.</p></li><li><p>Assist in conducting safety audits, inspections, and risk assessments.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate internal and external HSSEQ training activities.</p></li><li><p>Assist with incident reporting, investigation, and corrective action tracking.</p></li><li><p>Liaise with external partners, vendors, and authorities on HSSEQ matters.</p></li><li><p>Maintain HSSEQ documentation, records, and reports.</p></li><li><p>Support compliance with ISM, ISPS, and ISO standards where applicable.</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Diploma in HSE or a relevant Marine-related discipline.</p></li><li><p>Minimum 2 years of HSE experience, preferably within Marine or Shipping industry.</p></li><li><p>Strong interest and passion in HSE practices.</p></li><li><p>Good interpersonal and presentation skills.</p></li><li><p>Proficient in Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint.</p></li><li><p>Strong written and verbal communication skills in English.</p></li><li><p>Completed occupational health & safety training with hands-on HSEQ experience.</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of ISM, ISPS, incident investigation, and risk management is an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Internal Auditor certification for ISO 9001 / 14001 / 45001 preferred.</p></li></ul>",
